    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Half metal balls, which are filled with sand and covered with a layer of pitch. These form the basis for making chasing tools: the pitch fixes the object and forms a springy surface. By heating the pitch ball, the object is released. There are various recipes for making chasers pitch, but black or brown pitch is always the main ingredient.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
